// Semantic direction:
// deskriptiv_kompleksitet: Fagin (1974) — NP = ∃SO (second-order existential) over finite structures.
//   Immerman-Vardi: PTIME = FO + LFP over ordered structures.
// polynom_hierarki: PH = ⋃ Σᵖₖ — collapses if any level equals the one below.
// krets_kompleksitet: lower bounds are hard; no super-polynomial circuit lower bound for NP known.
// BPP_klasse: problems solvable in polynomial time with bounded two-sided error — likely = P.
// NC_klasse: polylogarithmic depth, polynomial work — efficiently parallelisable problems.
// kommunikasjonskompleksitet: two-party bit transmission needed to compute f(x,y) where Alice has x, Bob has y.
// kernelization: reduce instance to kernel of size g(k) in FPT time — FPT iff kernel exists.
// treewidth_FPT: many NP-hard problems become FPT when treewidth is bounded.
// resolution_kompleksitet: propositional resolution proof size; exponential lower bounds known for pigeon-hole principle.
// beregnbar_strukturteori: P-isomorphism conjecture — all NP-complete sets are p-isomorphic?

// Primitive flow:
// P ⊆ NP ⊆ PH ⊆ PSPACE ⊆ EXPTIME
// P ⊆ BPP (konjonktur: P = BPP via derandomisering)
// NL = coNL (Immerman-Szelepcsényi)
// FPT ⊆ W[1] ⊆ W[2] ⊆ ... ⊆ XP (parametrisert hierarki)

